FBIS3-10182 "drlat042_l_94001" FBIS-LAT-94-042 Document Type:Daily Report 3 Mar 1994 SOUTH AMERICA Bolivia Lieutenant Arrested in Death of Spanish Citizen PY0203204994 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1628 GMT 2 Mar 94 PY0203204994 Madrid EFE Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Text] La Paz, 2 Mar (EFE) -- Bolivian sources have reported that Bolivian Army Lieutenant Marco Antonio Mejia Alarcon was detained today, accused of murdering Spanish citizen Manuel Ramon Puchol Pastor. Puchol, 33, a Spanish judicial branch employee, died on 10 February in San Matias. According to several witnesses and a medical report, the Spanish citizen was beaten to death by a group of military men. The La Paz Government maintained until today the version that he had died of a cocaine overdose or that he had committed suicide.
